UXIN while it can be compared to carmax seems like it could be also compared to Truecar China does have a larger population than the US and the used car business is supposedly booming with some over saturation in some areas True car financials Revenue in Q4 of 2018 totaled 911 million up 10 over Q4 of 2017 and below our revenue guidance of 955 million to 975 million Through all of 2018 revenue was 3536 million up 9 over the prior yearSentiment from Chinese citizens so far from my understanding is that both Uxin and Guazi are the 2 largest used car platforms
